column18:
Welcome

 

Task and Procedure

Thanks for accepting the HIT! In this HIT, you will take approximately 10 mins to complete a math quiz. The quiz has two parts. In the first part, you will be asked to answer 5 easy math questions. After that, you can take a 20s break and then go to the second part, which includes 5 relatively difficult math questions. All of them are selected from SAT practice test.



You have 5 mins to complete the easy questions, and 5 mins for the difficult questions. To avoid guessing, it takes 30 seconds to enable the submit button in each part. For compensation, You will receive 5 cents as base payment, additionally, you will receive 20 cents for each correct answer in the easy part and 25 cents for each correct answer in the hard part.

 
Responses will be Confidential

All records from this study will be kept private. Your responses will not affect your current or future experience or relations with the University of Minnesota. In addition, in any sort of report we might publish, we will not include any information that makes it possible to identify you. Research records will be stored securely, and only researchers will have access to the records.

 
Contacts and Questions

This survey is being conducted by the GroupLens Research lab in the Computer Science and Engineering Department at the University of Minnesota. If you have any question about this study, please feel free to contact the researchers at zhan5963@umn.edu. 



Preparation

Please prepare pen and paper in advance, these questions require basic calculation, please do not use a calculator.

 



-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 

To check if you've understood the payment policy, please answer the below question. (warning: failing in this question may influence your final rewards)

 
How much you will receive if you answer 3 easy questions and 2 hard questions correctly?
